00:00:44.629 --> 00:00:47.214
<i><c.color80ffff>The legend of the ten rings</c>

00:00:47.423 --> 00:00:50.091
<i><c.color80ffff>has been told for thousands of years.</c>

00:00:51.969 --> 00:00:56.431
<i><c.color80ffff>Every generation,
the story grows.</c>

00:00:56.599 --> 00:01:01.394
<i><c.color80ffff>But at its centre
there is always one man.</c>

00:01:10.112 --> 00:01:16.952
<i><c.color80ffff>Some say he found the rings in a crater
or stole them from a tomb.</c>

00:01:19.705 --> 00:01:22.540
<i><c.color80ffff>They gave him the strength of a god,</c>

00:01:22.708 --> 00:01:26.211
<i><c.color80ffff>and the gift of eternal life.</c>

00:01:32.760 --> 00:01:36.388
<i><c.color80ffff>He could have used them for good.</c>

00:01:40.810 --> 00:01:42.978
<i><c.color80ffff>But all he wanted...</c>

00:01:43.145 --> 00:01:44.854
<i><c.color80ffff>was power.</c>

00:02:26.939 --> 00:02:30.483
<i><c.color80ffff>He called his army The Ten Rings.</c>

00:02:32.695 --> 00:02:37.824
<i><c.color80ffff>Over the centuries, they spread
into every corner of the world.</c>

00:02:45.166 --> 00:02:47.959
<i><c.color80ffff>They moved in the shadows...</c>

00:02:50.338 --> 00:02:52.380
<i><c.color80ffff>Toppled governments...</c>

00:02:54.925 --> 00:02:56.968
<i><c.color80ffff>And changed the course of history.</c>

00:03:13.194 --> 00:03:17.489
<i><c.color80ffff>He chased money and power
for a thousand years.</c>

00:03:18.324 --> 00:03:21.451
<i><c.color80ffff>But he still wanted more.</c>

00:03:26.791 --> 00:03:28.541
Have you heard the legend of Ta Lo?

00:03:29.960 --> 00:03:34.839
<i><c.color80ffff>A hidden village with mythical creatures
and ancient magic.</c>

00:03:35.007 --> 00:03:39.969
Where people practise
a martial arts style from the gods.

00:03:40.262 --> 00:03:42.013
<i><c.color80ffff>I want to find it.</c>

00:03:42.181 --> 00:03:45.642
Of course. I'll send a scout
to explore the area,

00:03:45.810 --> 00:03:48.436
<i><c.color80ffff>and come back
with more information.</c>

00:03:50.689 --> 00:03:52.565
I want to go now.

00:04:16.173 --> 00:04:17.340
The forest...

00:04:19.301 --> 00:04:21.928
...is moving.

00:04:52.126 --> 00:04:55.837
<i><c.color80ffff>He had nothing left
on Earth to conquer.</c>

00:04:59.967 --> 00:05:04.471
<i><c.color80ffff>That's when he came
for my home.</c>

00:05:13.564 --> 00:05:15.815
Where's the entrance
to Ta Lo?

00:05:17.568 --> 00:05:19.861
You're not welcome
in our village.

00:05:21.447 --> 00:05:23.573
You don't know who
you're talking to.

00:05:24.158 --> 00:05:25.825
I don't care who you are.

00:05:26.535 --> 00:05:30.371
Turn around now,
and I won't have to hurt you.

00:05:38.839 --> 00:05:40.340
Is that all?

00:07:59.813 --> 00:08:02.315
<i><c.color80ffff>That was the first time
I met your father.</c>

00:08:06.070 --> 00:08:09.822
<i><c.color80ffff>He was the last person
I thought I'd fall for.</c>

00:08:11.742 --> 00:08:14.577
<i><c.color80ffff>But love had other plans.</c>

00:08:18.248 --> 00:08:20.541
Shang-Chi,

00:08:20.709 --> 00:08:23.503
there's much more to know
about the legend of the rings,

00:08:23.671 --> 00:08:27.465
but you'll learn about that
when you're older.

00:08:28.133 --> 00:08:33.346
If Dad's rings were so powerful,
how did you beat him?

00:08:35.057 --> 00:08:41.854
Where I'm from, we are empowered
by the magic of the Great Protector.

00:08:46.568 --> 00:08:49.195
When you have the heart
of our dragon,

00:08:49.363 --> 00:08:52.407
you can do some amazing things.

00:08:52.991 --> 00:08:55.868
Can you still do those things?

00:08:57.746 --> 00:09:01.958
I left those powers in Ta Lo
with our dragon,

00:09:02.126 --> 00:09:05.586
but what I got in return
is so much better.

00:09:09.675 --> 00:09:11.843
I want you to have this.

00:09:13.637 --> 00:09:15.847
Whenever you feel lost,

00:09:16.014 --> 00:09:19.016
this will help you
find your way home.

00:09:19.810 --> 00:09:21.269
Can you remember that?

00:09:41.248 --> 00:09:42.457
Okay.

00:10:44.603 --> 00:10:45.603
Hello, sir,

00:10:45.729 --> 00:10:48.064
welcome to the Fairmont...

00:10:48.565 --> 00:10:49.565
I'm driving.

00:10:49.733 --> 00:10:51.192
No, you're not... Katy.

00:10:51.360 --> 00:10:53.236
Hey, hey, get back here.

00:10:53.320 --> 00:10:54.362
Give me the key.

00:10:55.864 --> 00:10:58.199
Please open the door.

00:10:58.283 --> 00:11:00.827
Oh, my God.

00:11:01.119 --> 00:11:02.954
- Get out.
- You get in!

00:11:03.038 --> 00:11:04.080
Look, if happens
to this thing,

00:11:04.164 --> 00:11:05.164
we're gonna be jobless

00:11:05.332 --> 00:11:06.499
and in debt
for the rest of our lives.

00:11:06.667 --> 00:11:08.751
Oh, come on. Nothing's gonna
happen to this car.

00:11:08.919 --> 00:11:10.336
I'm the Asian Jeff Gordon.

00:11:10.504 --> 00:11:11.671
I don't know who that is.

00:11:11.839 --> 00:11:13.631
Most career wins
in all of NASCAR history?

00:11:13.799 --> 00:11:15.299
Please get out of the car.

00:11:15.759 --> 00:11:16.759
Shaun,

00:11:16.885 --> 00:11:18.970
we've been friends
for 10 years, okay?

00:11:19.137 --> 00:11:21.180
<i><c.color80ffff>You know I'm not an idiot.</c>

00:11:21.640 --> 00:11:24.392
Please, get in. I'll go slow.

00:11:26.979 --> 00:11:28.688
Katy, watch the...

00:11:35.404 --> 00:11:36.404
<i><c.color80ffff>I knew Katy was trouble</i></c>

00:11:36.488 --> 00:11:37.822
<i><c.color80ffff>the first day we met
in high school.</i></c>

00:11:38.031 --> 00:11:39.073
I was getting picked on a lot,

00:11:39.157 --> 00:11:41.075
for all the reasons
we all get picked on a lot.

00:11:41.577 --> 00:11:42.952
<i><c.color80ffff>Plus, I had just moved
to the US,</c>

00:11:43.036 --> 00:11:44.495
<i><c.color80ffff>so I was struggling
with my English,</c>

00:11:44.663 --> 00:11:45.746
and I was on my way
to lunch one day

00:11:45.831 --> 00:11:47.665
when this guy
who was like twice my size

00:11:47.749 --> 00:11:48.749
yells at me
from down the hall,

00:11:48.834 --> 00:11:50.126
"What's up, Gangnam Style?"

00:11:50.878 --> 00:11:52.753
So I yelled back,
"I'm not Korean, idiot. "

00:11:52.838 --> 00:11:53.838
And I turn the corner,

00:11:53.922 --> 00:11:55.548
and I see this guy
drop his backpack,

00:11:55.716 --> 00:11:56.966
<i><c.color80ffff>he's getting
all up in his face...</c>

00:11:57.134 --> 00:11:58.926
And right before he was about
to throw the first punch,

00:11:59.094 --> 00:12:00.928
Katy comes out of nowhere,

00:12:01.096 --> 00:12:04.348
steps right between us
and starts screaming the lyrics

00:12:04.433 --> 00:12:05.850
<i><c.color80ffff>to Hotel California.</i></c>

00:12:06.018 --> 00:12:07.018
What?

00:12:07.185 --> 00:12:09.228
It's the art of confusion.
Works great on stupid people.

00:12:09.438 --> 00:12:10.479
<i><c.color80ffff>And that's how we met.</c>

00:12:10.647 --> 00:12:12.064
Then I pulled him
into the parking lot...

00:12:12.232 --> 00:12:13.357
At which point she revealed

00:12:13.442 --> 00:12:15.735
that she had also swiped
the keys to the guy's Mustang.

00:12:15.903 --> 00:12:17.987
<i><c.color80ffff>Yeah, we went on a little
joyride around the block.</c>

00:12:18.071 --> 00:12:19.530
And your wife
was in the car, too.

00:12:19.698 --> 00:12:21.324
- That's true. You were.
- What?

00:12:21.408 --> 00:12:22.825
I was just in the back seat.

00:12:22.910 --> 00:12:23.910
That's a part of the car.

00:12:23.994 --> 00:12:25.077
That's still
a part of the car.

00:12:25.162 --> 00:12:26.787
How have you
never told me this story?

00:12:26.955 --> 00:12:28.122
You know,
before she was a lawyer,

00:12:28.206 --> 00:12:29.457
your girl was pretty wild.

00:12:29.708 --> 00:12:31.292
Oh! What happened?

00:12:33.128 --> 00:12:34.295
I grew up.

00:12:34.880 --> 00:12:36.088
What's that supposed to mean?

00:12:36.173 --> 00:12:37.173
Yeah, what's that
supposed to mean?

00:12:37.257 --> 00:12:38.925
That maybe there's a point

00:12:39.009 --> 00:12:40.968
where you're supposed
to stop going on joyrides

00:12:41.136 --> 00:12:43.554
<i><c.color80ffff>and start thinking about
living up to your potential.</c>

00:12:43.722 --> 00:12:45.222
Please tell me
you're kidding, Soo.

00:12:45.390 --> 00:12:46.390
<i><c.color80ffff>Look,</c>

00:12:46.600 --> 00:12:47.642
we're now living in a world

00:12:47.726 --> 00:12:48.726
where at any moment

00:12:48.810 --> 00:12:50.561
half the population
can just disappear.

00:12:51.313 --> 00:12:53.564
<i><c.color80ffff>Life's too short
and too fragile.</c>

00:12:53.732 --> 00:12:55.316
Katy, you're a valet driver

00:12:55.400 --> 00:12:56.859
with an honours degree
from Berkeley,

00:12:57.027 --> 00:12:59.278
and Shaun can speak,
like, four languages.

00:12:59.446 --> 00:13:01.364
You've always been the most
talented people I know.

00:13:01.531 --> 00:13:03.616
I just don't get why
you're scared

00:13:03.700 --> 00:13:05.576
to actually use it
for something serious.

00:13:06.286 --> 00:13:07.286
<i><c.color80ffff>Wow.</i></c>

00:13:08.163 --> 00:13:10.873
You sound like my mom.
You also...

00:13:11.041 --> 00:13:12.375
dress like her
a little bit, too.

00:13:12.459 --> 00:13:14.502
<i><c.color80ffff>Where's this from, Talbots?</c>

00:13:14.586 --> 00:13:16.504
We're not running
from adulthood.

00:13:16.672 --> 00:13:18.965
How is it running to have jobs
that you actually like?

00:13:19.132 --> 00:13:20.633
Yeah, that doesn't
even make any sense.

00:13:20.717 --> 00:13:23.094
Did you think
valet parking is easy?

00:13:23.261 --> 00:13:25.179
It's like the most
challenging job ever.

00:13:25.263 --> 00:13:27.515
You need people skills,
driving skills...

00:13:27.724 --> 00:13:29.225
Soo can't even
parallel park.

00:13:32.896 --> 00:13:35.564
Well, it's almost midnight.
We got the early shift.

00:13:36.149 --> 00:13:38.734
Should probably be
responsible, go to sleep.

00:13:38.902 --> 00:13:40.611
Yeah, we can be responsible.
We can do that.

00:13:40.779 --> 00:13:42.238
Or...

00:13:42.406 --> 00:13:46.117
<i><font color=Lime>♪ Over,
sideways and under on a... ♪</i></c>

00:13:46.284 --> 00:13:48.494
<i><font color=Lime>♪ Take my horse
to the old town road ♪</i></c>

00:13:48.578 --> 00:13:49.578
<i><font color=Lime>♪ I'm gonna ♪</i></c>

00:13:49.663 --> 00:13:51.789
<i><font color=Lime>♪ Close my eyes ♪</i></c>

00:13:52.541 --> 00:13:53.624
<i><font color=Lime>♪ I don't wanna... ♪</i></c>

00:14:27.534 --> 00:14:28.659
Morning, Mrs Chen.

00:14:28.827 --> 00:14:29.952
She's not ready yet.

00:14:30.120 --> 00:14:31.787
Come have some joe
while you wait.

00:14:33.457 --> 00:14:35.416
Katy, Shaun's here.

00:14:35.584 --> 00:14:37.334
Yeah, Mom,
be there in a minute.

00:14:37.419 --> 00:14:38.419
Ruihua,

00:14:38.503 --> 00:14:41.005
you're supposed to be helping
your dad stock the shop.

00:14:41.173 --> 00:14:44.341
Mom, I can't work on an empty
stomach, my legs get crampy.

00:14:44.509 --> 00:14:45.885
Maybe Shaun can help him

00:14:45.969 --> 00:14:48.179
instead ofjust showing up
every day to eat our food.

00:14:48.346 --> 00:14:49.555
I'm happy to help.

00:14:49.723 --> 00:14:52.433
No, it's Ruihua's job,
let him do it.

00:14:53.101 --> 00:14:54.143
Waipo.

00:14:55.312 --> 00:14:56.937
That seat's for Waigong.

00:14:57.564 --> 00:14:59.106
Oh, sorry.

00:14:59.191 --> 00:15:04.612
He's getting all his favourite things
this year for the Day of the Dead.

00:15:04.780 --> 00:15:06.363
Are you sure
that Waigong's allowed to take

00:15:06.448 --> 00:15:07.448
Funyuns and cigarettes

00:15:07.532 --> 00:15:08.741
back to the afterlife?

00:15:08.825 --> 00:15:10.576
He can take anything.

00:15:10.744 --> 00:15:14.747
Last year I put a bottle of whisky
on his grave...

00:15:15.123 --> 00:15:16.832
And it was gone the next morning.

00:15:18.168 --> 00:15:21.420
I know you kids think it's silly.

00:15:21.505 --> 00:15:23.297
We don't think
it's silly, Waipo.

00:15:23.924 --> 00:15:25.966
We just know Waigong would've
wanted you to move on

00:15:26.051 --> 00:15:27.134
and enjoy your life.

00:15:27.219 --> 00:15:29.428
"Moving on"
is an American idea.

00:15:29.596 --> 00:15:31.764
You're American, Mom!
Don't forget.

00:15:32.349 --> 00:15:33.349
Shaun,

00:15:33.517 --> 00:15:36.685
did my daughter apply
to any newjobs this week?

00:15:36.853 --> 00:15:38.604
She really likes her job.

00:15:38.772 --> 00:15:39.855
We both do.

00:15:41.024 --> 00:15:42.817
Waigong didn't move here
from Hunan

00:15:42.984 --> 00:15:44.527
so you could park cars
for a living.

00:15:46.488 --> 00:15:47.571
Well, on that note,

00:15:47.656 --> 00:15:49.115
I think we're gonna
miss our bus.

00:15:50.325 --> 00:15:52.076
I'm sorry
for my unacceptable job.

00:15:52.244 --> 00:15:53.536
And for staying out late
last night,

00:15:53.620 --> 00:15:55.162
trying to enjoy my life.

00:15:55.622 --> 00:15:57.498
But one day, I'll make you
proud, I promise.

00:15:57.666 --> 00:15:59.041
I'm proud of you, sis.

00:15:59.209 --> 00:16:01.669
Parking cars is super hard.

00:16:01.878 --> 00:16:02.878
Thanks, bro.

00:16:02.963 --> 00:16:04.213
Maybe one day you'll pass
your driver's test,

00:16:04.297 --> 00:16:05.297
live the dream like me.

00:16:05.465 --> 00:16:06.465
Come on, Shaun, let's go.

00:16:09.928 --> 00:16:11.887
When are you two going
to get married?

00:16:11.972 --> 00:16:13.264
Waipo, we're just friends.

00:16:14.432 --> 00:16:16.976
All right. Go, go, go.

00:16:24.776 --> 00:16:26.944
Look. Look at that.
Look at that girl.

00:16:27.112 --> 00:16:29.029
She's writing a research paper
on a bus.

00:16:29.531 --> 00:16:30.531
So?

00:16:30.615 --> 00:16:32.032
That is exactly the daughter

00:16:32.117 --> 00:16:33.868
my mom wishes
came out of her vagina.

00:16:35.537 --> 00:16:37.580
I'm sorry about her.

00:16:39.166 --> 00:16:40.166
How's it goin'?

00:16:44.212 --> 00:16:46.505
Give me the pendant,

00:16:46.673 --> 00:16:48.799
and no one gets hurt.

00:16:49.509 --> 00:16:50.968
<i><c.color80ffff>Do you know this guy?</c>

00:16:52.429 --> 00:16:54.096
I don't know what
you're talking about, dude.

00:16:55.640 --> 00:16:57.808
Hey! Get off of me!

00:16:58.518 --> 00:17:00.019
What is wrong with you,
asshole?

00:17:00.145 --> 00:17:02.229
I don't want any trouble.

00:17:02.314 --> 00:17:04.148
Then give us the pendant!

00:17:04.316 --> 00:17:05.983
<i><c.color80ffff>You have the wrong guy!</c>

00:17:06.151 --> 00:17:07.401
Does he look like
he can fight?

00:17:07.485 --> 00:17:09.111
Come on, bro!

00:17:18.371 --> 00:17:19.371
You okay?

00:17:35.055 --> 00:17:36.931
Yo, what up, y'all?
It's your boy Klev,

00:17:37.098 --> 00:17:38.766
<i><c.color80ffff>comin' at you live on the bus.</c>

00:17:38.934 --> 00:17:40.226
<i><c.color80ffff>I actually did take</c>

00:17:40.310 --> 00:17:42.144
<i><c.color80ffff>a little bit of martial arts
as a youth,</c>

00:17:42.354 --> 00:17:45.105
so I'm gonna try and grade
this fight as we're goin'.

00:17:58.995 --> 00:18:00.496
Holy shit.

00:18:01.706 --> 00:18:03.123
Who are you?

00:18:17.931 --> 00:18:19.014
You got this, bro!

00:18:22.978 --> 00:18:23.978
My bad.

00:18:49.462 --> 00:18:50.629
No, no, no!

00:18:52.048 --> 00:18:53.215
Sorry.

00:18:55.051 --> 00:18:56.093
What the hell's going on?

00:18:56.219 --> 00:18:57.303
You really wanna talk
about this now?

00:19:04.644 --> 00:19:06.020
Bus driver is down.

00:19:06.187 --> 00:19:07.354
I'm not gonna handle this.

00:19:07.522 --> 00:19:09.773
Every time I've tried to drive
a bus, I get yelled at.

00:19:29.878 --> 00:19:31.045
Go, you freak!

00:20:23.390 --> 00:20:24.681
Open the door, please!

00:20:28.645 --> 00:20:30.104
The back is about to go.

00:20:30.271 --> 00:20:32.314
On my signal,
make a hard right.

00:20:32.482 --> 00:20:33.482
What signal?

00:21:02.971 --> 00:21:04.388
Everybody to the front now!

00:21:05.765 --> 00:21:07.099
Go! Go, go, go.

00:21:07.976 --> 00:21:09.893
What's up, y'all? What's up,
y'all? What's up, y'all?

00:21:21.197 --> 00:21:23.615
You and your sister
deserve what's coming.

00:21:48.641 --> 00:21:50.058
Hold on, everybody!

00:21:50.310 --> 00:21:51.310
Oh, God.

00:21:59.611 --> 00:22:01.445
Oh, my God!

00:22:14.334 --> 00:22:15.959
Sorry. Heh.

00:22:16.753 --> 00:22:18.086
We make a good team.

00:22:48.451 --> 00:22:49.868
Shaun. Hey.

00:22:50.703 --> 00:22:52.621
You need to tell me
what the hell's going on.

00:22:52.789 --> 00:22:54.373
What are you doing?
Where are you going?

00:22:54.541 --> 00:22:56.208
- Macau.
- Macau?

00:22:56.292 --> 00:22:57.584
Those guys are going
after my sister next,

00:22:57.669 --> 00:22:58.669
and I have to
get to her first.

00:22:59.504 --> 00:23:00.879
You have a sister?

00:23:01.047 --> 00:23:02.047
Look, I know
this is confusing.

00:23:02.131 --> 00:23:03.382
I'll explain it
when I get back, I promise.

00:23:03.466 --> 00:23:04.466
No, no.

00:23:04.551 --> 00:23:05.634
Hell no, dude.

00:23:05.802 --> 00:23:06.969
This is bullshit!

00:23:07.136 --> 00:23:09.471
I have been by your side
for half your life.

00:23:09.639 --> 00:23:11.640
I get there are things you
never wanted to talk about,

00:23:11.724 --> 00:23:13.183
and I never wanted to push.

00:23:13.685 --> 00:23:16.353
But a guy with a freaking
machete for an arm

00:23:16.521 --> 00:23:18.438
just chopped
our bus in half, Shaun!

